description.narrative: UNICEF focused not only on increasing quality of services but the continuity of services during the challenging COVID epidemic, prioritizing both upstream developments of critical strategies and guidelines and downstream adaptation of approaches to reaching the most underserved and at-risk communities, seeing a remarkable improvement in reaching coverage of skilled attendance, postnatal care and immunization despite the challenges. Quality will be a major focus of capacity building efforts moving forward, especially care arrangements during and immediately after delivery and filling gaps in routine immunization based on the immunization improvement roadmap. | Status:Partially Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020
